==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ovenbird
<hw>Ov"en*bird`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<sd>(a)</sd> <def>Any species of the genus <gen>Furnarius</gen>, allied
to the creepers. They inhabit South America and the West Indies, and
construct curious oven-shaped nests.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>In the
United States, <spn>Seiurus aurocapillus</spn>; -- called also
<altname>golden-crowned thrush</altname>.</def> <sd>(c)</sd> <def>In
England, sometimes applied to the willow warbler, and to the long-tailed
titmouse.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>ovenware</ent>⟦br⟧
